headline: UHS raises revenue guidance for 2025
summary: The operator increased its outlook after posting earnings growth in the third quarter, aided by strong demand for services in its acute business and a newly approved Medicaid state supplemental payment program.

headline: Universal Health Services (UHS) Profit Margin Gains Challenge Cautious Growth Narratives
summary: Universal Health Services (UHS) has posted a standout year, with annual earnings growth hitting 34%, far surpassing its five-year average of 4.8%. Net profit margins climbed to 8.1% from last year's 6.7%, signaling enhanced profitability, and shares now trade at a 10.1x Price-To-Earnings Ratio, which is well below both the sector and peer averages. Despite slower revenue and earnings forecasts compared to the overall US market, the combination of improved margins, strong recent profit growth,...
